a fleet of jet powered cars. And it's interesting

00:47:08.770 --> 00:47:09.770
they'd been working on jets since 1950. They
put a jet engine in a car in 1953 and they

00:47:09.770 --> 00:47:10.770
finally decided that they had one that was
so practical that anybody could drive it.

00:47:10.770 --> 00:47:11.770
So they built a fleet of 50 cars and loaned
them out to the public as like a big publicity

00:47:11.770 --> 00:47:12.770
stunt. And so you could actually send a postcard
to Chrysler and if they drew your name and

00:47:12.770 --> 00:47:13.770
decided that, you'd-you'd get a car for three
months that was jet powered.

00:47:13.770 --> 00:47:14.770
And so housewives and accountants and just
average Joe Americans were getting these jet

00:47:14.770 --> 00:47:15.770
cars and they all looked identical, they were
all painted this-this turbine bronze color.

00:47:15.770 --> 00:47:16.770
They were very, they were a specific built
car so it's very unusual looking and they

00:47:16.770 --> 00:47:17.770
sounded really funky. And so for two years
these cars were all over the place. They had

00:47:17.770 --> 00:47:18.770
them on display at the World's Fair.

00:47:18.770 --> 00:47:19.770
I mean I-I-I was very young but I remember
seeing 'em in traffic. You couldn't miss 'em

00:47:19.770 --> 00:47:20.770
'cause of the sound they made. At the end
of the program, Chrysler rounded them all

00:47:20.770 --> 00:47:21.770
up and destroyed 'em all. And they saved a
couple, but they destroyed most of them. And

00:47:21.770 --> 00:47:22.770
it's one of those stories that ever since
I was a little kid it's always bugged me what

00:47:22.770 --> 00:47:23.770
happened to those cars and why.

00:47:23.770 --> 00:47:24.770
[laughter]

00:47:24.770 --> 00:47:25.770
And it's one of those things that I sort,
I've always been thinking and thinking and

00:47:25.770 --> 00:47:26.770
thinking about it and I ran into somebody
who knew some of the people working in the

00:47:26.770 --> 00:47:27.770
program and started interviewing these people
and I realized this is actually a really,

00:47:27.770 --> 00:47:28.770
really interesting story there.

00:47:28.770 --> 00:47:29.770
